div.span: Logs are stored in a file on a local disk and in a database in batches (queue_size). The local file is rotated every 1000000 events/logs. Rotation consists of creating a new file, compressing the old file and sending the compressed file to S3 bucket. Compression and sending to S3 are executed asynchronously.
